controllers.gui

Class Authentication

  • java.lang.Object
    • play.mvc.Results
      • play.mvc.Controller
        • controllers.gui.Authentication
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    play.mvc.Http.HeaderNames, play.mvc.Http.Status

    @Singleton
public class Authentication
extends play.mvc.Controller
    Controller that deals with login/logout. There are two login views: 1) login HTML page, and 2) an overlay. The second one is triggered by a session timeout or an inactivity timeout in JavaScript.

      • signInWithGoogle

        public play.mvc.Result signInWithGoogle(play.mvc.Http.Request request)
                                 throws java.security.GeneralSecurityException,
                                        java.io.IOException
        HTTP POST Endpoint for the login form. It handles the sign-in / log-in of users via Google OAuth sign-in button. The actual authentication is done with Google's gsi/client JavaScript library in the browser. Here we just check the Token ID, create the user if it doesn't exist yet und log in the user into JATOS. More info: https://developers.google.com/identity/gsi/web
        Throws:
        java.security.GeneralSecurityException
        java.io.IOException
